---
import ProductLayout from '../../../layouts/ProductLayout.astro';
---

<ProductLayout title="ST101A Desktop Static Eliminator Blower | ESD Control | DGSDK"
  description="ST101A desktop static eliminator blower for localized ESD control in electronics, SMT, and precision assembly. Adjustable airflow, stable ionizing output."
  image="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a.webp">
  <section class="product-detail-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/products">Products</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/products/static-eliminator">Static Eliminator</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>ST101A</span>
      </div>

      <div class="product-top">
        <div class="product-gallery">
          <div class="product-main-image slider-wrapper">
            <button class="slider-arrow left" id="prevImage">‹</button>
            <img
              id="mainProductImage"
              src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a.webp"
              alt="ST101A Table Ionizing Air Blower"
            />
            <button class="slider-arrow right" id="nextImage">›</button>
          </div>

          <div class="product-thumbs">
            <img
              class="thumb-image active-thumb"
              src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a.webp"
              alt="ST101A Thumbnail 1"
              data-full="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a.webp"
            />
            <img
              class="thumb-image"
              src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a2.jpg"
              alt="ST101A Thumbnail 2"
              data-full="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a2.jpg"
            />
            <img
              class="thumb-image"
              src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a3.jpg"
              alt="ST101A Thumbnail 3"
              data-full="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a3.jpg"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="product-summary">
          <h1>ST101A Table Ionizing Air Blower</h1>
          <p class="product-short-desc">
            Compact desktop ionizing air blower designed for localized static elimination,
            convenient installation, and adjustable airflow control.
          </p>

          <div class="product-actions">
            <button class="quote-btn" type="button">Get a Quote</button>
            <a href="https://wa.me/61436605126" target="_blank" class="whatsapp-btn">WhatsApp</a>
          </div>

          <div class="product-highlights">
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>Compact Size</h4>
              <p>Suitable for desktop use and small workspace environments.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>Adjustable Airflow</h4>
              <p>Flexible air volume control for different static control needs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-item">
              <h4>Stable Output</h4>
              <p>Built-in high-voltage generator for reliable ion performance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Description</h2>
        <p>
          Static charge on work surfaces, components, and materials causes dust attraction,
          assembly errors, and ESD damage — problems that are particularly costly in electronics
          assembly, SMT, and precision manufacturing environments. The ST101A Table Ionizing Air
          Blower is designed to neutralize these charges at close range, directly at the workstation.
        </p>
        <p>
          Using AC ionization technology, the ST101A generates a balanced stream of positive and
          negative ions that effectively neutralize surface static within its working range.
          Its compact desktop form factor makes it easy to position at assembly stations, inspection
          benches, or packaging lines without occupying valuable floor space.
        </p>
        <p>
          The unit is convenient to move and install, supports adjustable ionized airflow,
          and is suitable for electronics assembly, inspection benches, packaging, and
          small-area industrial anti-static applications.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Desktop model for easy positioning and operation</li>
          <li>Adjustable air volume for flexible usage conditions</li>
          <li>Built-in high-voltage generator for reliable ion output</li>
          <li>Suitable for small-area static elimination tasks</li>
          <li>Convenient installation and maintenance</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Technical Advantages</h2>
        <div class="advantage-grid">
          <div class="advantage-card blue">
            <h3>Desktop Friendly</h3>
            <p>Compact model is ideal for bench-level and workstation anti-static control.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card yellow">
            <h3>Adjustable</h3>
            <p>Variable air volume improves adaptability for different applications.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card green">
            <h3>Dependable</h3>
            <p>Integrated high-voltage system supports steady ionization performance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
        <div class="spec-table-wrap">
          <table class="spec-table">
            <tr><td>Operating Voltage</td><td>110V / 60Hz or 220V / 50Hz</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Current Consumption</td><td>0.25A or 0.12A</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Operating Temperature</td><td>-10℃ to 50℃</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Size</td><td>90mm(L) × 170mm(W) × 260mm(H)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Weight</td><td>3.3Kg</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Air Volume</td><td>45–110CFM</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Ion Balance</td><td>0V ±10V</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Air Coverage</td><td>40cm × 60cm</td></tr>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Industry Applications</h2>
        <div class="application-tags">
          <span>Electronics Assembly</span>
          <span>Workstations</span>
          <span>Testing Benches</span>
          <span>Packaging</span>
          <span>Precision Assembly</span>
          <span>Small-Scale Production</span>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Electronics Assembly Workstations</h3>
            <p>Static charge on PCBs, ICs, and passive components can cause latent ESD damage that only shows up during field testing. Positioning the ST101A at each operator's bench continuously neutralizes charge buildup on components, tools, and work surfaces without requiring operators to change their workflow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Optical Inspection Benches</h3>
            <p>Dust attracted to statically charged lenses, films, and glass panels is one of the leading causes of false defect readings and rework. The ST101A's localized ionized airflow displaces charged dust particles before they can settle, reducing false rejection rates and improving yield.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Packaging and Labeling Lines</h3>
            <p>Plastic films, shrink wrap, and label substrates accumulate significant static charge during handling. The ST101A eliminates this charge at the packaging station, preventing labels from misaligning, films from clinging, and finished products from attracting contamination.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>How to Choose the Right Ionizing Blower</h2>
        <p>The ST101A is the right choice when you need targeted static control at a single workstation within a compact desktop footprint. If your work surface exceeds 40cm × 60cm, or you need to cover multiple adjacent stations, consider the <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-104a">ST104A Horizontal Ion Blower</a> (60cm × 120cm coverage) or the <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-1200">ST1200</a> for full-width line coverage. For inline conveyor applications, an <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-e-series">ion bar</a> is usually more appropriate than a blower.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is an ionizing air blower used for?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">An ionizing air blower neutralizes static electricity on surfaces, components, and materials by generating balanced positive and negative ions. It prevents dust attraction, ESD damage, and assembly errors in electronics manufacturing and precision production.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How close does the ST101A need to be to the work surface?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST101A is most effective at a working distance of 20–60 cm from the target. Its air coverage area of 40 cm × 60 cm makes it ideal for individual workstations and desktop-level applications.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How does the ST101A differ from an ion bar?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST101A is a fan-type blower that actively projects ionized air toward a work surface. An ion bar is a linear electrode strip suited for inline conveyor applications. Blowers are better for workstations; ion bars suit continuous production lines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the ST101A require compressed air?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">No. The ST101A has a built-in fan and requires only a standard power outlet — 110V/60Hz or 220V/50Hz. No compressed air supply is needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How often does the ST101A need cleaning or maintenance?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The emitter needles should be cleaned every 1–3 months depending on your environment. Regular cleaning keeps ion balance within the specified 0V ±10V range. No specialized tools are required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can the ST101A be used in cleanroom environments?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The ST101A is suitable for cleanroom-adjacent and controlled environments. For ISO-classified cleanrooms, please contact us to confirm compatibility with your specific cleanliness class requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <div class="related-slider-wrap" data-current="st-101a">
          <div class="related-slider-header">
            <h2>Related Products</h2>
            <div class="related-slider-nav">
              <button class="related-slider-btn related-slider-prev" type="button">‹</button>
              <button class="related-slider-btn related-slider-next" type="button">›</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="related-slider-track">
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-g-series" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-g-series">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-g.jpg" alt="ST-G Series" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST-G Series Intelligent Ion Rod</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-e-series" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-e-series">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-e.jpg" alt="ST-E Series" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST-E Series Intelligent Ion Rod</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-f-series" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-f-series">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-f.jpg" alt="ST-F Series" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST-F Series Intelligent Ion Rod</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-s200" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-s200">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-s200.jpg" alt="ST-S200" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST-S200 Mini Ionizer Fan</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-101a" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-101a">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-101a.webp" alt="ST101A" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST101A Table Ionizing Air Blower</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-104a" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-104a">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-104a.jpg" alt="ST104A" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST104A Horizontal Ion Blower</h4>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/static-eliminator/st-1200" class="related-slide-card" data-key="st-1200">
              <img src="/assets/img/static-eliminator/st-1200.jpg" alt="ST1200" loading="lazy" />
              <h4>ST1200 Horizontal Ion Fan</h4>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>

